## Output Requirements
- Module name: `{{ ir.module }}_spec`; bind line: `bind {{ ir.module }} {{ ir.module }}_spec spec_inst(.*);`
- Ports must match the DUT exactly (same names, widths, directions)
- All assertions inside `always @(posedge clk) begin ... end` blocks
- Use `assert(<expr>)` only — never `assert property(...)` or any SVA property syntax
- No `function`, `task`, or `class` declarations anywhere in the module — use `wire`/`assign` for decode logic
- Guard temporal assertions with `$past(...)` and explicit conditions; never assume a
  previous state without checking it
- Include a `$past` validity guard: wrap any `$past()`-using assertion in
  `if ($past(1'b1))` or a real signal guard to suppress the first-cycle X
- Emit the full JSON object as the ONLY output (no markdown fences, no explanation)
